      "date": "2019-07-05 17:02:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nFor $MOUNT_OPTS, the \"-o\" is assumed to be there. So, for this test, we could:\nmount_client $MOUNT \"$MOUNT_OPTS,ro\"\nor\nMOUNT_OPTS=$(csa_add \"-o $MOUNT_OPTS\" -o ro)\nor\ngo through the code and see if we should add \"-o \" to the beginning of MOUNT_OPTS. Some routines like zconf_mount() and zconf_mount_clients() adds the \"-o\" before using MOUNT_OPTS.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
